      "source_markdown": "### FADE IN:\n\n### SC1: EXT. BLACKRIDGE OBSERVATORY - NIGHT [00:00:00-00:00:38]\n\nA storm rolls over the mountain. The abandoned observatory turns slowly, powered by emergency lights.\n\n**NARRATOR**\n(quiet, cinematic)\nThe last signal on Earth did not come from the sky. It came from under the mountain.\n\n**MARA REYES**\n(urgent whisper)\nJonah, keep the drone low. If the dish sees us, the whole valley wakes up.\n\n**JONAH VALE**\n(nervous, trying to joke)\nGreat. Sneaking past a telescope that apparently has a temper. Completely normal night.\n\n> **SFX**: Rain hits metal. A distant servo motor groans.\n\n`ON SCREEN: SIGNAL LOCK - 03%`\n\n### SC2: INT. OBSERVATORY CONTROL ROOM - NIGHT [00:00:38-00:01:18]\n\nDusty monitors flicker. A blue waveform crawls across every screen.\n\n**DIRECTOR VALE**\n(over comms, controlled anger)\nMara, the artifact is broadcasting through every emergency channel. Shut it down before the city hears it.\n\n**MARA REYES**\n(focused)\nCopy that. I need thirty seconds and a miracle with a working battery.\n\n**AI VOICE**\n(calm, synthetic)\nWarning. Unauthorized biological intent detected.\n\n**SECURITY TEAM**\n(overlapping radio voices)\nSouth stairwell clear. East door jammed. Moving to intercept.\n\n> **MUSIC**: Low strings pulse faster.\n\n### SC3: INT. SUBTERRANEAN ARRAY - NIGHT [00:01:18-00:02:00]\n\nA black glass cylinder hums in the center of a circular chamber.\n\n**JONAH VALE**\n(awed, afraid)\nThat thing is not a transmitter. It's listening.\n\n**MARA REYES**\n(steady, decisive)\nThen we stop talking.\n\n**ANTAGONIST - CAEL ORRIN**\n(smooth, threatening)\nYou are already too late. The signal learned your voices before you found the door.\n\n> **SFX**: Power surges. Glass resonates.\n\n`ON SCREEN: VOICEPRINTS COPIED`\n\n**MARA REYES**\n(fierce)\nNot mine. I changed the password.\n\n**NARRATOR**\n(soft, rising tension)\nFor one second, the mountain went silent. Then every speaker in Blackridge began to breathe.",
